Commentary Text: Harpreet Brar to Kohli, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! What a great take by Jitesh. Harpreet Brar fired this full around the leg stump line, Virat tried to paddle it fine, but it pitched just it front of his bat and lobbed off the bottom of the bat. Jitesh dived to his left and took it one-handed. Luckily the ball had enough air-time for the keeper to react. RCB may not mind this wicket actually. They want their power hitters for a power finish! Commentary Text: Parnell to Prabhsimran, out Bowled!! Was there reverse on that? Looked like it. Parnell angled it on a length from round the wicket, trusted his pace and seam position to do the trick. Prabhsimran was in a hurry to go for a big shot. Commentary Text: Vijaykumar Vyshak to Sam Curran, out Sam Curran Run Out!! Pins the yorker outside off, Curran squeezes it wide of backward point and rushes through for a quick single. Has he made it though? Yikes! He's caught short at the bowling end. Curran doesn't want to watch the replays, he is clearly embarrassed and walks back with an air of guilt surrounding him. It was hit to the left of backward point and Hasaranga was quick to latch on and send in a bullet-like throw. A bit of lazy running from the Kings' skipper meant he couldn't make it. A dive would have surely helped, but wasn't to be. Sam Curran run out (Hasaranga) 10(12) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Vijaykumar Vyshak to Prabhsimran, out Harpreet Singh Run Out!! Yes-no, stranded and Siraj smashes the stumps with a direct-hit and breaks into CR7's Siiuuu celebration. What a gun throw. Prabhsimran stepped out and lofted the drive to the right of mid-off. He saw Siraj attack to his right. Wow the throw looks even better on the replay. Had to pick it up and release in one go and off balance. Power throw. Tell you, the bowlers do have a great arm. Virat enjoyed that bit of fielding and he is roaring in full voice. Harpreet Singh run out (Siraj) 13(9) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Siraj to Livingstone, out Lbw!! Big appeal for LBW, not given. Long discussion and reviewed. Impact is the only thing that can save Livingstone here because he advanced down the pitch. Line wise that's surely in line. Could be too far down. No bat as well as UltraEdge stays silent. Wowww. Hitting. This is one of the best reviews in cricket recently. All odds against the call. Batter a long way down the pitch, was impact too far away, was it too high? But Siraj believed. He roared and pleaded for the finger to go up. You can totally understand the ump saying no onfield. Virat turned to Siraj. The bowler demanded, DK ran to Virat with 8 odd seconds left. Virat had a quick glance at the timer as it was ticking while DK was giving his inputs and with 1 second on the timer Virat says yes, case referred. Ball-tracker said impact in line, impact not too far away from the stumps and hitting top of middle and leg. Siraj roars, the roar of victory and achievement. RCB are winning the PP quite easily. Faf had to cut short his sideline interview because of the review and he claps for this DRS call with mic in one hand. RCB on fire! Livingstone lbw b Siraj 2(4)

Commentary Text: Siraj to Atharva Taide, out Lbw!! What a gun bowler Siraj has turned into. Tests, then bossed the ODIs, now is making a strong case in the T20 format too. Wrap him in cotton please. The obvious inswinger to the left-hander from Siraj, did it pitch in line was the question. The ump said no despite a really strong appeal. RCB discussed and signalled the T. Replays confirmed no edge. Pitching in line, hitting in line and smashing leg stump to let RCB into a roar. The head fell too far across for Atharva and he was found out. Atharva Taide lbw b Siraj 4(2) [4s-1]
